data.reasoningText:
I can see the issue. The page is rendering the svgl-layout's content (a sidebar with navigation items) but the `.page` divs from the flow page are not visible.

Looking at the CSS:
```css
.page {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100vh;
    background: white;
    ...
}
```

The `.page` elements are `position: absolute`, but they're inside the `.app` div which doesn't seem to have `position: relative` or a defined size. Also the `.app` div has `background: var(--bg-card)` but the commented CSS shows the app should have `position: relative; width: 100%; height: 100vh;`.
I found the root cause—the `.app` container's positioning styles are commented out in the +page.svelte file, so it has no positioning context for the absolutely positioned `.page` elements to anchor to. Let me look at the layout file to understand the structure better.

